content.problem:
In circle $O$, central angle $\angle AOB$ measures $70°$.

1. Find $m\widearc{AB}$ (the minor arc).

2. Find $m\widearc{ADB}$ (the major arc through point $D$).

center
tikzpicture[scale=1.3]
 (0,0) circle (1.5);
 ll[AtlasTeal] (0,0) circle (2pt) node[below] {$O$};

 ll[AtlasTeal] (35:1.5) circle (2pt) node[above right] {$A$};
 ll[AtlasTeal] (-35:1.5) circle (2pt) node[below right] {$B$};
 ll[AtlasTeal] (180:1.5) circle (2pt) node[left] {$D$};

 (0,0) – (35:1.5);
 (0,0) – (-35:1.5);

 (0.4,0) arc (0:35:0.4);
 at (0.5,0.15) { $70°$};
tikzpicture
center

