In the figure, $\overline{AB}$ is a diameter of circle $O$, and 
$C$ is a point on the circle. If $AC = 5$ and $BC = 12$, find $AB$.

center
tikzpicture[scale=0.9]
 (0,0) circle (2);
 (A) at (-2,0);
 (B) at (2,0);
 (C) at (1.2,1.6);

 (A) – (B);
 (A) – (C) – (B);

 ll[AtlasTeal] (A) circle (2pt) node[left] {$A$};
 ll[AtlasTeal] (B) circle (2pt) node[right] {$B$};
 ll[AtlasTeal] (C) circle (2pt) node[above] {$C$};

 at (-0.4,0.8) {$5$};
 at (1.6,0.8) {$12$};

 % Right angle mark
 ($(C)!0.15!(A)$) – ++(0.1,-0.15) – ($(C)!0.15!(B)$);
tikzpicture
